<!-- 
 Copyright (c) 2012, Oracle and/or its affiliates. All rights reserved. 

   NAME
     config_subscriber_preferences_map.xml - For piggyback notifications(Active Mediation)

   DESCRIPTION
     For Active Mediation Feature:
     This XML is used to seed the subscriber preferences into the /config/subscriber_preferences_map obj.
     Each Subscriber Preference has an unique prefernce ID. OOB the subscriber preferences are:
     Language, Channel, Time of Notification, 
     Notification Expiry - Number of days before which notification must be sent, 
     Notification Interval - Interval between each notification,
     Streaming Threshold  - Value given in MB, notification for every MB of usage of data,
     Resource ID for Streaming Thresholds.

     Each field is read as follows:
     Name . Name of the preference
     ID . ID associated with the preference
     Type . The type of value that the preference can assume. 
       .	STR [1]
       .	INT [2]
       .	ENUM [3] List of Values which the user can choose from. Example Different channels, Languages etc.
       .	DECIMAL [4]
       .	TSTAMP [5]
     String ID . The ID in the strings_t class which would be associated with the localized string associated with the preference. 
                 This would be read by the customer center to display the preference name in a localized string form.
     String Version: The version of the string ID specified.
                     Domain: active_mediation
     Default . This field would contain the default value that the preference can assume. In case of ENUM, this field will 
               contain STRING_ID of the value in VALUES array.
     

     NOTE: For localization, the STRING_ID and STR_VERSION must map to an entry in strings_t table 
           for the domain: active_mediation 
     
   MODIFIED   (MM/DD/YY)
   sdoddi      01/19/12 - Creation

-->
